commentary: Cameron-Dow to Najibullah Zadran, OUT hits it straight back! Oh this freefall doesn't stop for Afghanistan. A classic fingerspinner's dismissal. Lobbed up at a length outside off, getting him to try and drive against the turn. He looks to do that, without coming close to the pitch of the ball. It floats back to the bowler who takes a simple catch. Another Afghanistan batsman out playing with hard hands

commentary: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, OUT Ireland might have their breakthrough! Yes! Asghar Afghan is diving awkwardly at the striker's end and is caught short by a direct hit. He's tumble and done something to either his shoulder or bicep. On his feet now, but he'll have to go. Just nowhere near completing a risky run. Short of a length just outside off, sliced into the covers and he isn't even close enough to ground his bat as Dockrell swoops down on this - after it was parried towards him by point - and hits the stumps on the bounce. Afghanistan had just begun to put some pressure on Ireland, but they've given it all away. Another good innings from their captain comes to an end
shortText: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, OUT

Short of a length just outside off, sliced into the covers and he isn't even close enough to ground his bat as Dockrell swoops down on this - after it was parried towards him by point - and hits the stumps on the bounce. Afghanistan had just begun to put some pressure on Ireland, but they've given it all away. Another good innings from their captain comes to an end

commentary: Aftab Alam to O'Brien, OUT another one dragged one! Cross bat shots haven't been a wise choice here, that was short on middle, he went for the pull, with little choice but to attack, ends up chopping it back onto his stumps and Afghanistan are just two away, with Ireland's only hope now back in the hut

commentary: Aftab Alam to Murtagh, OUT through the gate and that's another one for Aftab! kept it simple, kept it straight, bowled it fast and he was too late too bring his bat down, which also came down at an angle, as the ball crashed into middle stump. He's on a hat-trick and will fancy his chances
